{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban all face coverings at all protests and demonstrations",
        "additional_details": "Peaceful protest is a fundamental right, but it must be exercised responsibly. When people conceal their identity, we believe it undermines trust, enables anti-social behaviour, and limits effective policing. A consistent, no-exceptions rule would provide clarity, deter disorder, and protect both the public and those taking part in lawful demonstrations.",
        "background": "Face coverings at protests allow individuals to hide their identity, making it harder to prevent and investigate crime, disorder, and intimidation. We call for a clear, universal ban on face coverings at protests to ensure accountability and public safety.",
        "closed_at": null,
